1. There are two groups being compared, group A and group B.
2. Serum IL-10 levels were measured in both groups.
3. Serum E-selectin levels were measured in both groups.
4. The serum IL-10 levels in group A were lower than those in group B.
5. The difference in serum IL-10 levels between group A and group B is statistically significant (P<0.05).
6. The serum E-selectin levels in group A were lower than those in group B.
7. The difference in serum E-selectin levels between group A and group B is statistically significant (P<0.05).
